{"title": "Greek Literature", "description": "\"The Greeks were the most intellectual people of the old world. \u2026 The study of Greek literature is therefore a proper element in a liberal education. The Greek language, naturally flexible and rich in poetical words, becomes in the hands of the great writers a medium of unequalled force, clearness, and adaptability, able to express as well the highest aspirations of the poet as the subtlest shades of philosophical argument or the most abstruse technicalities. The books of Greece have passed the critical selection of the ages, and the student, unencumbered by masses of inferior material, can approach the works of acknowledged masters, the true fountain-head of European culture.\" - Summary taken from the Introduction", "duration": 9522, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "16006", "name": "Henry Julius Wetenhall Tillyard"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/greekliterature_2108_librivox/greekliterature_2108.jpg", "copyright_year": "1914", "genres": ["Literary Criticism", "Social Science (Culture & Anthropology)"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Devorah Allen"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Devorah Allen"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Leni"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Introduction", "readers": [11084], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/greekliterature_2108_librivox/greekliterature_00_tillyard_64kb.mp3", "duration": 188}, {"section": 1, "title": "Homer and the Epic", "readers": [16197], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/greekliterature_2108_librivox/greekliterature_01_tillyard_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1126}, {"section": 2, "title": "Lyric, Elegiac, and Iambic Poetry", "readers": [16115], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/greekliterature_2108_librivox/greekliterature_02_tillyard_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1242}, {"section": 3, "title": "Tragedy", "readers": [8722], "path": "https://ww